# SBFSpot

## Documentation
https://hub.docker.com/r/solarexplorer/sbfspot-sqlite

## Commands used to create the dockers

* sudo docker create -t  -v /etc/localtime:/etc/localtime:ro  -v /var/sbfspot/data:/var/smadata  -v /var/sbfspot/config/SBFspot.cfg:/opt/sbfspot/SBFspot.cfg  --device=/dev/tty  --net=host  --name sbfspot-daydata  solarexplorer/sbfspot-sqlite /opt/sbfspot/SBFspot -v -ad1 -am0 -ae1
* sudo docker create -t  -v /etc/localtime:/etc/localtime:ro  -v /var/sbfspot/data:/var/smadata  -v /var/sbfspot/config/SBFspot.cfg:/opt/sbfspot/SBFspot.cfg  --device=/dev/tty  --net=host  --name sbfspot-monthdata  solarexplorer/sbfspot-sqlite /opt/sbfspot/SBFspot -v -sp0 -ad0 -am1 -ae1 -finq

## fetch data

*/5 6-22 * * * docker start -a sbfspot-daydata
55 05 * * * docker start -a sbfspot-monthdata

## upload

docker run -dt --restart=unless-stopped \
 -v /etc/localtime:/etc/localtime:ro \
 -v /var/sbfspot/data:/var/smadata \
 -v /var/sbfspot/config/SBFspotUpload.cfg:/opt/sbfspot/SBFspotUpload.cfg \
 --name sbfspot-uploader \
 solarexplorer/sbfspot-sqlite /opt/sbfspot/SBFspotUploadDaemon

# SBFSpot

## Documentation
https://hub.docker.com/r/solarexplorer/sbfspot-sqlite

## Build custom image with MQTT support

The base image is based on Debian Stretch (EOL) and does not include `mosquitto-clients`,
which is required for MQTT publishing. Build a custom image first:

```bash
sudo docker build -t sbfspot-mqtt .
```

## Commands used to create the containers

```bash
sudo docker create -t \
  -v /etc/localtime:/etc/localtime:ro \
  -v /var/sbfspot/data:/var/smadata \
  -v /var/sbfspot/config/SBFspot.cfg:/opt/sbfspot/SBFspot.cfg \
  --device=/dev/tty \
  --net=host \
  --name sbfspot-daydata \
  sbfspot-mqtt /opt/sbfspot/SBFspot -v -ad1 -am0 -ae1 -mqtt

sudo docker create -t \
  -v /etc/localtime:/etc/localtime:ro \
  -v /var/sbfspot/data:/var/smadata \
  -v /var/sbfspot/config/SBFspot.cfg:/opt/sbfspot/SBFspot.cfg \
  --device=/dev/tty \
  --net=host \
  --name sbfspot-monthdata \
  sbfspot-mqtt /opt/sbfspot/SBFspot -v -sp0 -ad0 -am1 -ae1 -finq
```

Note: `-mqtt` is only added to `sbfspot-daydata` since that is the container
providing the 5-minute spot data. Month data collection does not need it.

## Fetch data (crontab)
*/5 6-22 * * * docker start -a sbfspot-daydata
55 05 * * * docker start -a sbfspot-monthdata

## Upload to PVOutput

```bash
docker run -dt --restart=unless-stopped \
  -v /etc/localtime:/etc/localtime:ro \
  -v /var/sbfspot/data:/var/smadata \
  -v /var/sbfspot/config/SBFspotUpload.cfg:/opt/sbfspot/SBFspotUpload.cfg \
  --name sbfspot-uploader \
  sbfspot-mqtt /opt/sbfspot/SBFspotUploadDaemon
```

## SBFspot.cfg MQTT settings
```ini
MQTT_Publisher=/usr/bin/mosquitto_pub
MQTT_Host=localhost
MQTT_Topic=sbfspot_{serial}
MQTT_ItemFormat="{key}": {value}
MQTT_ItemDelimiter=,
MQTT_PublisherArgs=-h {host} -t {topic} -m "{{message}}"
MQTT_Data=Timestamp,InvStatus,EToday,ETotal,PACTot,PDC1,PDC2,UDC1,UDC2,InvTemperature
```

## Home Assistant MQTT sensors
See `sbfspot_sensors.yaml` for the sensor configuration.
